In <1992Feb13.023613.22345@demon.co.uk> aph@cix.compulink.co.uk (Andrew Haley) writes:

>Ralph, what is the current status of Khufu and Khafre?
>We certainly could do with efficient software encryption functions,
>and yours seem to be appropriate.

>A major problem with these algorithms seems to be that an initial
>random S-box needs to be agreed by both parties.
>[etc]

Actually a much bigger problem with the algorithms is that they have been
patented by Xerox.  This is a real shame since they are great encryption
functions (fast, simple, (as far as I know) secure, etc), but since they're
tied up in patents noone can use them.

